- They're cold.

759
00:38:30,894 --> 00:38:32,862
Yeah, I'm offering it short,

760
00:38:32,896 --> 00:38:34,864
but it has like I want to do it
for Armenia,

761
00:38:34,898 --> 00:38:37,142
for the hosts
and for the khash makers.

762
00:38:37,176 --> 00:38:39,247
Okay. Good.

763
00:38:44,701 --> 00:38:49,257
Cheers. Cheers. Welcome.

764
00:38:49,292 --> 00:38:51,881
Joining Serj and I at the table

765
00:38:51,915 --> 00:38:54,470
are George, his longtime
manager and friend,

766
00:38:54,504 --> 00:38:57,749
Malina, the proprietor
of the place,

767
00:38:57,783 --> 00:38:59,889
and Sam, a restaurateur
from Yerevan,

768
00:38:59,923 --> 00:39:03,341
along with some friends.

769
00:39:03,375 --> 00:39:06,723
Khash is what hipster goofs
these days

770
00:39:06,758 --> 00:39:08,691
would call bone broth,

771
00:39:08,725 --> 00:39:14,317
basically a stock flavored
by roasted beef bones.

772
00:39:16,284 --> 00:39:18,045
